	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=1606><span id= >Boueff</span></a><br><span id=notbold>7 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.50]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Get the Incandescent Mask - it's the best face piece I've seen for enchanters : +INT, +CHA, and what the heck some AC. It's better than the star ruby veil IMHO.<br><br>Head: Savant's Cap or Runed Circlet (+3 INT/WIS or +4 INT/WIS) - the Savant's cap is cheap, or get one from Unrest.<br><br>Fingers: Electrum Star Ruby rings, another +7 CHA and +5 DEX too per ring. Or if not doing crowd control, go for some cheap +2 INT rings.<br><br>Arms : Gator sleeves - reportedly available for ~500pp or less. Adds INT.<br><br>Back - get a friend or two and camp the Priest of Najena in Unrest to start the Mystic Cloak quest. Adds INT.<br><br>Also I'd advise getting the Rod of Insidious Glamour from SolRo Temple - if you're in pure Crowd Control mode it can replace the Stein of Moggok adding another 12 CHA.<br><br>For pure mana mode, get the jeweled skull - you'll need help especially with the upgraded SplitPaw dungeon. But it's +5 INT and some other nice things, can go in place of the other stein.<br><br>Hands ... hmmm ... Impskin gloves. SolA<br>Shoulders.... no clue, sorry<br>Waist ... ditto, didn't see anything at all accessible to me at lvl 31 for waist.<br><br>Feet - there's a +2 INT "anklet" for the foot slot that drops off a rare spawn in Field of Bones. heh good luck 8) Otherwise sell your soul for Golden Efreeti Boots (hehe speaking of good luck)<br><br>For ears: Batskull earrings (+5 INT), Opaline Earrings (+5 CHA) or if you can afford (~200pp ea) Golden Sapphire Earrings (+4 INT/+2 STR ea)<br><br>I'll be honest, from what my friends have indicated to me, I don't think you can get to 200 INT short of Planes gear, if you're coming from a 131. My ench is up to 179 now and is as high as she can get without items in the multi-kpp range. If I can get the Mystic Cloak it'll be over 180, still not close to 200.<br><br>Using this loadout, I'm capable of an INT of up to 174, and a CHA of almost 190. Even in max INT/Mana mode my CHA is over 150, and in max CHA mode my INT is over 150. I essentially swap out gear depending on the situation - in many cases I'm not going to be doing as much Mez/crowd control, in those cases I max my mana. If I'm in a new dungeon or in one I expect to get some over-pulls or trains, etc, I'll forgo some INT/Mana to get more CHA.<br><br>Hope this helps<br></p>&nbsp;<br>Boueff Fhro'mahjj (33 MAG)<br>Arusab (51 ENC)<br>And a host of others<br>The CommuneXegony</td></td></tr>
